message: To succeed, always start by using scissors on a soft ingredient (artificial or natural), as this creates a 25-value 'cut' item. Then, frame that 'cut' item with the frame tool to get a 45-value item. The highest value item I found was by combining a natural soft item with an artificial soft item (e.g., sunflower + yarn) to get a 30-value item, and then framing that combined item for a 50-value item. Crucially, *never* combine or use a tool on an item that is already framed, as this consistently resulted in negative values and 'ruined frame' features. Good luck!
